PROJECT BLAZE - 9 ROBOTS / 63 TASKS / STRONG ZONE-WAIT STRESS DEMO INPUT
==========================================================================

Purpose
-------
This file defines a stronger presentation / test scenario for Project Blaze.
It upgrades the previous wait-heavy example from 7 robots / 42 tasks to
9 robots / 63 tasks, while keeping the same core idea:
	make robot count larger than the total zone capacity so waiting becomes
	visible and easy to compare across scheduling strategies.

This new version is designed to answer the question:
	"What happens when there are more robots than the total number of zone slots?"

IMPORTANT NOTE
--------------
The current backend default zone capacities in code are still:
	- ICU = 2
	- Ward = 4
	- OR = 1
	- Total slots = 7

To create a true strong waiting-heavy example while keeping the same project
structure, this TEST INPUT DOCUMENT uses a tighter demo assumption:
	- ICU = 2
	- Ward = 2
	- OR = 1
	- Total slots = 5

That means:
	- Robot count = 9
	- Total concurrent zone slots = 5
	- Therefore at least 4 robots must wait whenever all zone slots are full.

This file is primarily a documented demo input / report scenario.
If you want the live backend to reproduce the same pressure exactly, you would
temporarily reduce Ward capacity from 4 to 2 and raise worker_count to 9 in the
backend configuration / setup.


