SECTION C - WHY THIS INPUT FORCES WAITING
-----------------------------------------
Because the total zone capacity is only 5 but there are 9 robots, the system can
never run more than 5 tasks at the same time in this example.

So the moment 5 compatible zone slots are occupied:
	- remaining robots do NOT stop existing as workers,
	- but they must block and wait at zone allocation,
	- which makes scheduler ordering much more visible in the demo.

This is exactly the kind of situation where the scheduling policy becomes easy to
compare and explain.


